module.exports = [
  // === Science and Research (125 entries) ===
  ["absorb","Science and Research","吸收","摄取物质","Certain chemical compounds can absorb carbon dioxide directly from the atmosphere offering a potential technological solution for reducing greenhouse gas concentrations at a global scale.","某些 chemical compounds 可以直接从 atmosphere 中 absorb carbon dioxide 为在全球范围内 reducing greenhouse gas concentrations 提供了一种 potential technological solution"],
  ["acid","Science and Research","酸","化学物质","Sulfuric acid is one of the most widely used industrial chemicals worldwide with applications ranging from fertilizer production to petroleum refining and wastewater treatment in numerous manufacturing processes globally.","Sulfuric acid 是全球使用最广泛的 industrial chemicals 之一 其 applications 涵盖从 fertilizer production 到 petroleum refining 和 wastewater treatment 的 numerous manufacturing processes globally"],
  ["activate","Science and Research","激活","启动反应","UV light can activate certain chemical catalysts that would otherwise remain completely inert and unreactive under normal ambient temperature and pressure conditions in a standard laboratory environment at room temperature.","UV light 可以 activate 某些在 normal ambient temperature and pressure conditions in a standard laboratory environment at room temperature 下否则会 remain completely inert and unreactive 的 chemical catalysts"],
  ["adaptation","Science and Research","适应","进化调整","The remarkable adaptation of certain deep-sea creatures to survive under crushing water pressure and in complete permanent darkness demonstrates the incredible resilience and diversity of life on our planet over evolutionary timescales spanning millions of years.","Certain deep-sea creatures survive under crushing water pressure and in complete permanent darkness 的 remarkable adaptation demonstrates the incredible resilience and diversity of life on our planet over evolutionary timescales spanning millions of years"],
  ["alkaline","Science and Research","碱性的","pH值","The soil samples collected from the volcanic region were found to be highly alkaline with a measured pH value exceeding eight point five making them unsuitable for growing most common agricultural crop varieties without extensive soil treatment and chemical amendment.","从 volcanic region 收集的 soil samples 被发现 highly alkaline 测量的 pH value exceeding eight point five 使得它们不适合在没有 extensive soil treatment and chemical amendment 的情况下 growing most common agricultural crop varieties"],
  ["alloy","Science and Research","合金","金属混合物","Steel is an alloy primarily composed of iron and a small but critically important percentage of carbon which dramatically increases the hardness tensile strength and overall durability of the resulting metallic material compared to elemental iron used alone.","Steel 是一种 alloy  primarily composed of iron and a small but critically important percentage of carbon 与单独使用的 elemental iron 相比 dramatically increases the hardness tensile strength and overall durability of the resulting metallic material"],
  ["amber","Science and Research","琥珀","化石树脂","Scientists have discovered perfectly preserved ancient insects trapped inside fossilized amber dating back over one hundred million years providing an extraordinary window into the biodiversity of prehistoric ecosystems during the age of the dinosaurs that once roamed the earth.","科学家在 fossilized amber 中发现了 perfectly preserved ancient insects trapped inside  date back over one hundred million years 为曾经在地球上 roam 的 dinosaurs age 期间 prehistoric ecosystems 的 biodiversity 提供了一个 extraordinary window"],
  ["anatomy","Science and Research","解剖学","身体结构","A thorough understanding of human anatomy is absolutely fundamental to the practice of medicine and surgery enabling doctors to accurately diagnose internal medical conditions and perform complex surgical operations safely without causing unintended damage to surrounding healthy organs and delicate vital tissues.","对人类 anatomy 的 thorough understanding 对医学和外科的实践 absolutely fundamental 使医生能够 accurately diagnose internal medical conditions 并 safely perform complex surgical operations 而不会对 surrounding healthy organs and delicate vital tissues 造成 unintended damage"],
  ["anomaly","Science and Research","异常","偏离正常","The research team detected an unusual magnetic anomaly deep beneath the ocean floor that geologists believe could potentially indicate the presence of a previously undiscovered massive deposit of valuable rare earth minerals essential for manufacturing modern electronic devices.","研究小组在 ocean floor  deep beneath 发现了一个 unusual magnetic anomaly 地质学家认为这可能 potentially indicate the presence of a previously undiscovered massive deposit of valuable rare earth minerals essential for manufacturing modern electronic devices"],
  ["applied","Science and Research","应用的","实际运用","Applied research focuses on solving specific practical problems in fields such as medicine engineering and agriculture whereas basic theoretical research aims primarily to expand fundamental human knowledge without any immediate commercial or practical application in mind initially.","Applied research 侧重于解决 medicine engineering and agriculture 等领域中的 specific practical problems 而 basic theoretical research 主要旨在 expand fundamental human knowledge  initially 没有任何 immediate commercial or practical application in mind"],
  ["asteroid","Science and Research","小行星","太空岩石","Scientists believe that a massive asteroid impact approximately sixty-six million years ago was the primary cause of the sudden mass extinction event that wiped out the dinosaurs along with roughly three-quarters of all plant and animal species then living on Earth in a geological instant.","科学家认为 approximately sixty-six million years ago a massive asteroid impact 是突然 mass extinction event 的 primary cause 这次事件 wiped out the dinosaurs 以及当时地球上生活的 roughly three-quarters of all plant and animal species in a geological instant"],
  ["atom","Science and Research","原子","物质微粒","An atom consists of a dense central nucleus containing positively charged protons and electrically neutral neutrons surrounded by a cloud of negatively charged electrons orbiting at various discrete energy levels determined by the fundamental laws of quantum physics governing the subatomic realm.","Atom 由一个 dense central nucleus 组成 其中包含 positively charged protons 和 electrically neutral neutrons 周围环绕着 negatively charged electrons cloud orbiting at various discrete energy levels determined by the fundamental laws of quantum physics governing the subatomic realm"],
  ["bacterium","Science and Research","细菌","微生物体","Each individual bacterium is a single-celled microscopic organism capable of reproducing rapidly under favorable environmental conditions with some species dividing into two identical daughter cells as frequently as every twenty minutes in ideal laboratory growth media at optimal temperatures.","每个 individual bacterium 都是一个 single-celled microscopic organism capable of reproducing rapidly under favorable environmental conditions 在 ideal laboratory growth media at optimal temperatures 中 一些物种 dividing into two identical daughter cells 的频率每二十分钟一次"],
  ["beam","Science and Research","光束","能量射线","Laser beam technology is now used in an incredibly diverse range of modern applications from precision surgical instruments in hospital operating rooms to high-speed fiber-optic data transmission systems carrying vast amounts of internet traffic across entire ocean floors between continents.","Laser beam 技术现在用于 incredibly diverse range of modern applications 从 hospital operating rooms 中的 precision surgical instruments 到在 continents 之间 across entire ocean floors carrying vast amounts of internet traffic 的 high-speed fiber-optic data transmission systems"],
  ["catalyst","Science and Research","催化剂","反应加速","A chemical catalyst works by lowering the activation energy barrier required for a particular reaction to proceed allowing the transformation of reactants into products to occur far more rapidly and at significantly lower temperatures than would otherwise be thermodynamically possible without its presence.","Chemical catalyst 通过 lowering the activation energy barrier required for a particular reaction to proceed 来工作 allowing the transformation of reactants into products to occur far more rapidly and at significantly lower temperatures than would otherwise be thermodynamically possible without its presence"],
  ["chromosome","Science and Research","染色体","遗传载体","Humans typically inherit twenty-three chromosome from each biological parent for a total complement of forty-six arranged in twenty-three matching pairs that carry all of the genetic instructions necessary for building and maintaining a complete functioning human body throughout life.","人类通常从每个 biological parent 继承 twenty-three chromosome 总共四十六条 arranged in twenty-three matching pairs 携带所有在终生中 building and maintaining a complete functioning human body 所必需的 genetic instructions"],
  ["circuit","Science and Research","电路","电子回路","Modern computer processor chips contain billions of microscopic transistor etched onto silicon wafers forming incredibly complex integrated circuit that process digital information at speeds measured in billionths of a second per individual logical operation performed.","Modern computer processor chips 包含数十亿个 microscopic transistor etched onto silicon wafers 形成 incredibly complex integrated circuit 以每个 individual logical operation performed 数十亿分之一秒的速度 processing digital information"],
  ["colleague","Science and Research","同行","科研合作","The research fellow presented her preliminary findings to a room of distinguished scientific colleague from universities and research institutes across twelve different countries at the major international academic conference held annually in Geneva Switzerland each spring.","Research fellow 在每年春天在 Geneva Switzerland 举行的 major international academic conference 上向来自十二个不同国家的 universities and research institutes 的 distinguished scientific colleague 介绍了她的 preliminary findings"],
  ["combustion","Science and Research","燃烧","氧化反应","Internal combustion engines convert the chemical energy stored in fossil fuels into useful mechanical work through a controlled series of rapid miniature explosions occurring inside the engine's sealed metal cylinders driving pistons that ultimately turn the vehicle's wheels through a complex transmission system.","Internal combustion engines 通过 controlled series of rapid miniature explosions occurring inside the engine's sealed metal cylinders 将 fossil fuels 中存储的 chemical energy convert 为 useful mechanical work 驱动活塞 最终通过 complex transmission system 转动车辆的 wheels"],
  ["condense","Science and Research","凝结","气体液化","When water vapor in the warm moist air rises and encounters cooler temperatures at higher altitudes it begins to condense into tiny liquid droplets that eventually gather together to form the visible clouds we can observe floating across the sky on any given day.","当 warm moist air 中的 water vapor 上升并 encounter cooler temperatures at higher altitudes 它开始 condense into tiny liquid droplets 最终聚集在一起 形成我们在任何 given day 可以 observe floating across the sky 的 visible clouds"],
  ["conductivity","Science and Research","导电性","传导能力","Copper is widely used in electrical wiring because of its excellent electrical conductivity second only to silver among all commercially available and economically practical metallic conductor materials suitable for large-scale industrial production and widespread commercial distribution.","Copper 因其 excellent electrical conductivity 被广泛用于 electrical wiring 在所有 commercially available and economically practical metallic conductor materials suitable for large-scale industrial production and widespread commercial distribution 中仅次于 silver"],
  ["conservation","Science and Research","守恒","能量守恒","The law of conservation of energy states that energy cannot be created or destroyed in an isolated system but can only be transformed from one form into another such as when chemical potential energy in food is converted into kinetic energy of muscle movement and body heat in living organisms.","Law of conservation of energy 指出在 isolated system 中 energy cannot be created or destroyed 只能从一种形式 transform 为另一种形式 如当 food 中的 chemical potential energy 被 convert 为 living organisms 中 muscle movement 和 body heat 的 kinetic energy 时"],
  ["constant","Science and Research","常数","恒定值","The speed of light in a vacuum is a fundamental universal constant of nature measuring approximately three hundred thousand kilometers per second and according to Einstein's famous theory of special relativity represents the absolute maximum speed at which any information or physical object can possibly travel through space.","真空中的光速是一个 fundamental universal constant of nature 测量为 approximately three hundred thousand kilometers per second 根据 Einstein's famous theory of special relativity 代表任何信息或物理物体在空间中 possibly travel 的 absolute maximum speed"],
  ["cosmos","Science and Research","宇宙","太空秩序","Modern astronomical observatories equipped with extremely sensitive instruments can now peer deep into the distant cosmos capturing faint light from galaxies that formed less than one billion years after the original Big Bang event that created our entire observable universe some thirteen point eight billion years ago.","配备 extremely sensitive instruments 的 modern astronomical observatories 现在可以 deep into the distant cosmos 捕获来自 some thirteen point eight billion years ago 原始 Big Bang event 后 less than one billion years formed 的遥远星系的 faint light"],
  ["crystal","Science and Research","晶体","有序结构","When a saturated solution of salt water is allowed to evaporate slowly over several days under carefully controlled laboratory temperature and humidity conditions beautiful cubic crystal of pure sodium chloride gradually form as the dissolved ions arrange themselves into a highly ordered repeating three-dimensional geometric lattice structure.","当 saturated solution of salt water 在 carefully controlled laboratory temperature and humidity conditions 下 slowly evaporate over several days 时 美丽的 cubic crystal of pure sodium chloride 逐渐形成 因为 dissolved ions arrange themselves into a highly ordered repeating three-dimensional geometric lattice structure"],
  ["decay","Science and Research","衰变","分解过程","Radioactive isotope used in medical imaging procedures undergo predictable nuclear decay over time emitting detectable subatomic particles that specialized scanning equipment can track to create detailed three-dimensional diagnostic images of internal organs and detect abnormalities like cancerous tumors at very early treatable stages.","用于 medical imaging procedures 的 radioactive isotope 随时间 undergo predictable nuclear decay  emitting detectable subatomic particles that specialized scanning equipment can track 以 create detailed three-dimensional diagnostic images of internal organs and detect abnormalities like cancerous tumors at very early treatable stages"],
  ["density","Science and Research","密度","质量体积","The density of a substance defined as its mass per unit volume determines whether an object made of that material will float or sink when placed in a particular liquid such as water which has a density of exactly one gram per cubic centimeter under standard laboratory reference conditions at four degrees Celsius.","Substance 的 density defined as its mass per unit volume 决定了由该 material 制成的 object 放置在 particular liquid 中时是 float 还是 sink 例如 water which has a density of exactly one gram per cubic centimeter under standard laboratory reference conditions at four degrees Celsius"],
  ["diffusion","Science and Research","扩散","分子运动","The process of diffusion causes particles to spread gradually from regions of higher concentration to regions of lower concentration through random thermal molecular motion until eventually a state of uniform equilibrium distribution has been reached throughout the entire available spatial volume of the container system.","Diffusion 过程导致 particles 通过 random thermal molecular motion 从 higher concentration 的区域 gradually spread 到 lower concentration 的区域 直到 eventually a state of uniform equilibrium distribution has been reached throughout the entire available spatial volume of the container system"],
  ["dilute","Science and Research","稀释","降低浓度","Chemists often need to dilute concentrated acid solutions by carefully and slowly adding precise measured volumes of the strong acid into a larger quantity of distilled water while constantly stirring the mixture to ensure even distribution and prevent dangerous localized overheating or violent splashing of corrosive liquid droplets.","Chemists 经常需要 dilute concentrated acid solutions 通过 carefully and slowly adding precise measured volumes of the strong acid into a larger quantity of distilled water 同时 constantly stirring the mixture 以确保 even distribution 并防止 dangerous localized overheating or violent splashing of corrosive liquid droplets"],
  ["dissect","Science and Research","解剖","仔细分析","Biology students learn to carefully dissect preserved animal specimens such as frogs and earthworms in order to observe and identify the various internal organ systems and understand how the different anatomical structures are interconnected and arranged spatially within a living vertebrate or invertebrate body.","Biology students 学习 carefully dissect preserved animal specimens such as frogs and earthworms 以 observe and identify the various internal organ systems 并 understand the different anatomical structures 如何在 living vertebrate or invertebrate body 内 interconnected and arranged spatially"],
  ["distill","Science and Research","蒸馏","分离纯化","The laboratory apparatus is designed to distill the crude liquid mixture by heating it to a carefully controlled temperature at which the desired volatile organic compound vaporizes and can then be collected and condensed back into purified liquid form in a separate receiving flask positioned at the cooler end of the glass condenser column apparatus.","Laboratory apparatus 设计用于 distill the crude liquid mixture 通过将其加热到 carefully controlled temperature 在该温度下 desired volatile organic compound vaporizes 然后可以 collected and condensed back into purified liquid form 在 a separate receiving flask positioned at the cooler end of the glass condenser column apparatus 中"],
  ["elastic","Science and Research","弹性的","可恢复形变","Rubber bands stretch when pulled because the long coiled polymer molecules that make up the rubber material are able to temporarily straighten and extend under applied tension but then immediately return to their original randomly coiled configuration once the stretching force is removed demonstrating the material property known as elastic reversible deformation behavior in response to mechanical stress.","橡皮筋在被拉时 stretch 因为构成 rubber material 的 long coiled polymer molecules 在 applied tension 下能够 temporarily straighten and extend 但然后在 stretching force removed 后 immediately return 到它们 original randomly coiled configuration  demonstrated the material property known as elastic reversible deformation behavior in response to mechanical stress"],
  ["electrode","Science and Research","电极","导电端子","In a standard laboratory electrochemical cell two different metal electrode are immersed in a conductive electrolyte solution and connected by an external wire allowing electrons to flow spontaneously from the more reactive metal anode to the less reactive metal cathode generating a measurable electrical potential difference and direct current flow between them.","在 standard laboratory electrochemical cell 中 two different metal electrode 被 immersed in a conductive electrolyte solution 并由 external wire connected  allowing electrons to flow spontaneously from the more reactive metal anode to the less reactive metal cathode generating a measurable electrical potential difference and direct current flow between them"],
  ["electron","Science and Research","电子","基本粒子","Electron microscope use beams of accelerated electron instead of visible light to create highly magnified images of extremely tiny objects such as individual virus particles and even large individual protein molecule at resolutions far beyond what any conventional optical light microscope could ever possibly achieve due to the physical limitations imposed by the wavelength of visible light itself.","Electron microscope 使用 beams of accelerated electron 而不是 visible light 来创建 extremely tiny objects 的 highly magnified images 例如 individual virus particles 甚至 large individual protein molecule 其 resolution far beyond 任何 conventional optical light microscope 由于 visible light 本身的 wavelength 所 imposed 的 physical limitations 而 ever possibly achieve"],
  ["equilibrium","Science and Research","平衡","动态稳定","A reversible chemical reaction reaches a state of dynamic equilibrium when the rate of the forward reaction converting reactants into products becomes exactly equal to the rate of the reverse reaction converting products back into reactants resulting in no further net observable change in the concentrations of any of the chemical species present in the reaction mixture over time.","Reversible chemical reaction reaches a state of dynamic equilibrium 当 converting reactants into products 的 forward reaction 的 rate 变得 exactly equal to converting products back into reactants 的 reverse reaction 的 rate 时 导致 over time no further net observable change in the concentrations of any of the chemical species present in the reaction mixture"],
  ["evaporate","Science and Research","蒸发","液体汽化","When liquid water is heated to its boiling point of one hundred degrees Celsius at standard atmospheric pressure at sea level the individual water molecules gain sufficient kinetic energy to overcome the intermolecular attractive forces holding them together and begin to rapidly evaporate transforming from the liquid phase directly into invisible gaseous water vapor that rises and disperses into the surrounding ambient air above the heated container.","当 liquid water 在 standard atmospheric pressure at sea level 下被加热到其 boiling point of one hundred degrees Celsius  individual water molecules 获得 sufficient kinetic energy 以 overcome 将它们 hold together 的 intermolecular attractive forces 开始 rapidly evaporate 从 liquid phase directly transform 为 invisible gaseous water vapor that rises and disperses into the surrounding ambient air above the heated container"],
  ["evolution","Science and Research","进化","生物演化","The theory of biological evolution by natural selection first proposed by Charles Darwin in 1859 explains how all the diverse species of life on Earth gradually arose and diversified over hundreds of millions of years from simpler common ancestral forms through the gradual accumulation of small inherited genetic variations that conferred even slight survival or reproductive advantages in particular local environments over successive generations.","1859年 Charles Darwin 首次提出的 biological evolution by natural selection 的理论解释了地球上所有 diverse species of life 如何在 hundreds of millions of years 中逐渐从 simpler common ancestral forms arise and diversified 通过 gradual accumulation of small inherited genetic variations 在 successive generations 中在 particular local environments 中 confer even slight survival or reproductive advantages"],
  ["exert","Science and Research","施加","用力作用","Magnets exert an invisible attractive or repulsive force on certain metallic objects made of iron nickel or cobalt that are located within their surrounding magnetic field region without requiring any direct physical contact between the magnet itself and the object being attracted or repelled across the intervening empty space separating them at a measurable distance apart.","Magnets 对位于其 surrounding magnetic field region 内的某些由 iron nickel or cobalt made 的 metallic objects exert an invisible attractive or repulsive force 而无需 magnet 本身与 being attracted or repelled across the intervening empty space separating them at a measurable distance apart 的 object 之间的 any direct physical contact"],
  ["experiment","Science and Research","实验","科学验证","The controlled laboratory experiment was meticulously designed to test the researchers' novel hypothesis by systematically varying only one independent experimental variable at a time while carefully keeping all other potentially confounding environmental factors and measurement conditions strictly constant and identical across all treatment groups and control comparison groups throughout the entire lengthy duration of the multi-year scientific investigation period.","Controlled laboratory experiment 被 meticulously designed 以 test the researchers' novel hypothesis 通过 systematically varying only one independent experimental variable at a time 同时 carefully keeping all other potentially confounding environmental factors and measurement conditions strictly constant and identical across all treatment groups and control comparison groups throughout the entire lengthy duration of the multi-year scientific investigation period"],
  ["fiber","Science and Research","纤维","细丝材料","Carbon fiber composite materials are exceptionally strong for their remarkably light weight and are now used extensively in aerospace engineering applications high-performance sporting equipment such as racing bicycles and modern wind turbine blades that must withstand enormous repeated mechanical stresses while rotating at high speeds in strong gusty winds for decades of continuous reliable operation.","Carbon fiber composite materials 相对于其 remarkably light weight 而言 exceptionally strong 现广泛用于 aerospace engineering applications high-performance sporting equipment such as racing bicycles 和 modern wind turbine blades that must withstand enormous repeated mechanical stresses 同时在 strong gusty winds 中以 high speeds rotating for decades of continuous reliable operation"],
  ["filter","Science and Research","过滤","分离筛选","The experimental protocol requires researchers to filter the crude reaction mixture through a fine porous membrane to remove all insoluble solid impurities and unwanted precipitate byproducts before the purified clear filtrate solution can be further analyzed using advanced spectroscopic and chromatographic analytical techniques to determine the precise chemical composition and yield of the desired product compound.","Experimental protocol 要求研究人员 filter the crude reaction mixture through a fine porous membrane 以在 purified clear filtrate solution can be further analyzed using advanced spectroscopic and chromatographic analytical techniques 之前 remove all insoluble solid impurities and unwanted precipitate byproducts 以 determine the precise chemical composition and yield of the desired product compound"],
  ["friction","Science and Research","摩擦力","运动阻力","Engineers constantly seek to reduce harmful friction between moving mechanical parts in engines and industrial machinery through improved lubrication systems advanced low-friction bearing designs and precisely engineered super-smooth surface finishes because excessive unwanted friction wastes enormous amounts of useful energy and causes premature mechanical wear and eventual catastrophic component failure if not properly managed and controlled over extended periods of heavy use.","工程师 constantly seek to reduce harmful friction between moving mechanical parts in engines and industrial machinery 通过 improved lubrication systems advanced low-friction bearing designs and precisely engineered super-smooth surface finishes 因为 excessive unwanted friction wastes enormous amounts of useful energy and causes premature mechanical wear and eventual catastrophic component failure if not properly managed and controlled over extended periods of heavy use"],
  ["fuse","Science and Research","熔化","融合接合","When heated to sufficiently high temperatures in a specialized industrial electric arc furnace the mixture of powdered raw mineral ingredients will gradually soften and eventually completely fuse together into a homogeneous molten glassy mass that upon subsequent controlled cooling and solidification forms the hard durable ceramic material with the desired combination of mechanical thermal and electrical insulation properties for the intended commercial application.","当在 specialized industrial electric arc furnace 中加热到 sufficiently high temperatures 时 powdered raw mineral ingredients 的混合物将 gradually soften 并 eventually completely fuse together 成为 homogeneous molten glassy mass 在随后的 controlled cooling and solidification 后形成 hard durable ceramic material 具有 intended commercial application 所需的 mechanical thermal and electrical insulation properties 的 desired combination"],
  ["galaxy","Science and Research","星系","恒星系统","Our home Milky Way galaxy is a vast rotating spiral-shaped collection of approximately two hundred to four hundred billion individual stars plus enormous clouds of interstellar gas and cosmic dust all held together by the mutual gravitational attraction of their combined enormous total mass spread across a disk-shaped region of space measuring over one hundred thousand light-years from one edge to the opposite far side.","我们的家园 Milky Way galaxy 是一个 vast rotating spiral-shaped collection of approximately two hundred to four hundred billion individual stars plus enormous clouds of interstellar gas and cosmic dust 全部由它们 combined enormous total mass 的 mutual gravitational attraction held together  spread across a disk-shaped region of space measuring over one hundred thousand light-years from one edge to the opposite far side"],
  ["gel","Science and Research","凝胶","半固态","The clear viscous gel formed when the hot liquid solution of dissolved gelatin protein molecules was allowed to cool slowly to room temperature over several hours demonstrating the reversible physical process of thermo-responsive sol-gel phase transition behavior that is characteristic of many natural and synthetic polymer materials under appropriate thermal and chemical environmental stimulus conditions.","当 dissolved gelatin protein molecules 的 hot liquid solution 在 over several hours 里 slowly cool to room temperature 时 形成了 clear viscous gel  demonstrated the reversible physical process of thermo-responsive sol-gel phase transition behavior that is characteristic of many natural and synthetic polymer materials under appropriate thermal and chemical environmental stimulus conditions"],
  ["gene","Science and Research","基因","遗传编码","Each gene along the DNA molecule contains the specific coded biochemical instructions needed for building a particular protein molecule that will perform a precise specialized function within the living cell such as acting as a biological enzyme to catalyze a specific metabolic reaction or serving as an essential structural component of the cell's internal architectural framework and mechanical support system.","DNA molecule 上的每个 gene 包含 building a particular protein molecule 所需的 specific coded biochemical instructions 该 protein molecule 将在 living cell 内 perform a precise specialized function 例如作为 biological enzyme  catalyze a specific metabolic reaction 或 serving as an essential structural component of the cell's internal architectural framework and mechanical support system"],
  ["generator","Science and Research","发电机","能量转换","An electrical generator works on the fundamental physical principle of electromagnetic induction discovered by Michael Faraday in 1831 converting useful rotational mechanical energy derived from spinning steam turbines or falling water into clean electrical power that can be efficiently transmitted through high-voltage cables over enormous distances to homes factories schools and businesses across entire continents and regions.","Electrical generator 根据 Michael Faraday 在1831年发现的 electromagnetic induction 的 fundamental physical principle 工作 将 spinning steam turbines or falling water derived 的 useful rotational mechanical energy convert 为 clean electrical power 可以通过 high-voltage cables efficiently transmitted over enormous distances 到 homes factories schools and businesses across entire continents and regions"],
  ["genome","Science and Research","基因组","全套遗传","The successful completion of the ambitious international Human Genome Project in 2003 after thirteen years of intensive collaborative research involving thousands of scientists across multiple countries produced the first complete map of all the approximately three billion chemical base pairs that make up the entire set of human genetic instructions carried within the nucleus of every nucleated cell in our bodies.","经过涉及 multiple countries 数千名科学家的 thirteen years of intensive collaborative research  ambitious international Human Genome Project 在2003年 successful completion 产生了第一份 complete map of all the approximately three billion chemical base pairs that make up the entire set of human genetic instructions carried within the nucleus of every nucleated cell in our bodies"],
  ["gravity","Science and Research","重力","万有引力","The force of gravity between any two objects in the universe is directly proportional to the product of their individual masses and inversely proportional to the square of the distance separating their respective centers according to Isaac Newton's elegant universal law of gravitation first published in his monumental scientific work the Principia Mathematica in the year 1687 at the dawn of the modern scientific revolution in physics.","根据 Isaac Newton 于1687年在他的 monumental scientific work the Principia Mathematica 中首次发表的 elegant universal law of gravitation  the force of gravity between any two objects in the universe is directly proportional to the product of their individual masses and inversely proportional to the square of the distance separating their respective centers"],
  ["helium","Science and Research","氦","惰性气体","Helium is the second lightest and second most abundant chemical element in the entire observable universe after hydrogen yet it is relatively rare on Earth because being an extremely light chemically inert noble gas it can readily escape our planet's gravitational pull and drift away into the vacuum of outer space over geological timescales spanning millions of years since the original formation of our solar system.","Helium 是整个 observable universe 中 second lightest 且 second most abundant 的 chemical element 仅次于 hydrogen 但它在地球上 relatively rare 因为作为 extremely light chemically inert noble gas 它可以 readily escape 我们 planet's gravitational pull and drift away into the vacuum of outer space over geological timescales spanning millions of years since the original formation of our solar system"],
  ["identical","Science and Research","相同的","完全一样","Identical twins develop from a single fertilized egg that splits into two separate embryos during the very earliest stages of embryonic development and therefore share virtually one hundred percent of their inherited genetic material making them natural clones of each other and uniquely valuable subjects for scientific research studies designed to disentangle the complex interacting influences of genetic inheritance versus environmental upbringing on human development behavior and disease susceptibility.","Identical twins 从 a single fertilized egg that splits into two separate embryos during the very earliest stages of embryonic development 发育而来 因此 share virtually one hundred percent of their inherited genetic material 使它们成为彼此的 natural clones 和 uniquely valuable subjects for scientific research studies designed to disentangle the complex interacting influences of genetic inheritance versus environmental upbringing on human development behavior and disease susceptibility"],
  ["ignite","Science and Research","点燃","引发燃烧","A single tiny spark of static electricity generated by friction between two insulating surfaces can sometimes be sufficient to ignite highly flammable vapors of volatile organic solvents such as gasoline or acetone that may have accidentally accumulated in poorly ventilated laboratory workspaces creating a potentially catastrophic fire or even a violent explosion hazard if adequate safety precautions are not strictly followed at all times by all laboratory personnel present.","由 two insulating surfaces 之间的 friction generated 的 a single tiny spark of static electricity 有时可能足以 ignite 高度 flammable 的 volatile organic solvents such as gasoline or acetone 的 vapors 这些 vapors 可能 accidentally accumulated 在 poorly ventilated laboratory workspaces 中 如果 adequate safety precautions are not strictly followed at all times by all laboratory personnel present 则 creating a potentially catastrophic fire or even a violent explosion hazard"],
  ["infrared","Science and Research","红外线","热辐射","Infrared thermal imaging cameras can detect minute differences in the surface temperature of objects and living bodies from a safe distance and are used extensively in applications as diverse as building energy efficiency inspections medical diagnostic screening for inflammation and fever and night vision equipment for military and law enforcement surveillance operations conducted under conditions of total darkness where visible light is completely absent and unavailable.","Infrared thermal imaging cameras 可以从 safe distance detect minute differences in the surface temperature of objects and living bodies 并广泛用于 applications as diverse as building energy efficiency inspections medical diagnostic screening for inflammation and fever and night vision equipment for military and law enforcement surveillance operations conducted under conditions of total darkness where visible light is completely absent and unavailable"],
  ["inherit","Science and Research","继承","遗传获得","Children inherit approximately half of their total genetic material from each biological parent through the process of sexual reproduction which randomly shuffles and recombines the parental DNA sequences during the formation of specialized egg and sperm reproductive cells ensuring that each offspring receives a unique and never-before-seen combination of inherited genetic variants and traits from both sides of their ancestral family lineage.","Children 通过 sexual reproduction 的过程 inherit approximately half of their total genetic material from each biological parent 该过程在 specialized egg and sperm reproductive cells 的 formation 过程中 randomly shuffles and recombines the parental DNA sequences 确保每个 offspring receives a unique and never-before-seen combination of inherited genetic variants and traits from both sides of their ancestral family lineage"],
  ["ion","Science and Research","离子","带电粒子","When common table salt dissolves in water the ionic bonds holding the sodium and chloride ion together in the solid crystal lattice structure are broken by the polar water molecules and the individual positively charged sodium cations and negatively charged chloride anions become separated from each other and surrounded by shells of tightly bound water molecules existing as freely moving independent hydrated ion dispersed throughout the entire volume of the resulting clear saline aqueous solution.","当普通食盐 dissolve in water 时 在 solid crystal lattice structure 中 holding the sodium and chloride ion together 的 ionic bonds 被 polar water molecules broken  individual positively charged sodium cations 和 negatively charged chloride anions 变得 separated from each other 并被 tightly bound water molecules 的 shells surrounded  existing as freely moving independent hydrated ion dispersed throughout the entire volume of the resulting clear saline aqueous solution"],
  ["isotope","Science and Research","同位素","原子变体","Radioactive isotope of certain chemical elements such as carbon-14 and uranium-235 have unstable atomic nuclei that spontaneously decay over predictable periods of time known as their characteristic half-lives transforming into more stable daughter nuclei while simultaneously emitting detectable subatomic particles and electromagnetic radiation in the process which scientists can measure and use for various practical applications including archaeological dating and medical diagnostic imaging of internal body structures.","某些 chemical elements 如 carbon-14 和 uranium-235 的 radioactive isotope 具有 unstable atomic nuclei 这些 nuclei spontaneously decay over predictable periods of time known as their characteristic half-lives  transforming into more stable daughter nuclei 同时 simultaneously emitting detectable subatomic particles and electromagnetic radiation in the process 科学家可以 measure 并用于 various practical applications including archaeological dating and medical diagnostic imaging of internal body structures"],
  ["kinetic","Science and Research","动能的","运动能量","The kinetic theory of gases explains the macroscopic observable properties of gases such as pressure temperature and volume in terms of the collective average behavior of enormous numbers of microscopic individual gas molecules in constant rapid random motion colliding elastically with one another and with the containing walls of their enclosure transferring momentum and energy back and forth in countless billions of individual molecular-scale interactions occurring every single second throughout the entire volume of the gas sample.","Kinetic theory of gases 根据 enormous numbers of microscopic individual gas molecules in constant rapid random motion colliding elastically with one another and with the containing walls of their enclosure 的 collective average behavior 解释气体的 macroscopic observable properties 如 pressure temperature and volume 在 the entire volume of the gas sample 中每秒钟发生 countless billions of individual molecular-scale interactions transferring momentum and energy back and forth"],
  ["laser","Science and Research","激光","集中光束","Laser technology produces an intense highly focused beam of coherent light in which all the individual light waves oscillate in perfect synchrony with one another at exactly the same precise wavelength and phase enabling applications that require extreme precision and concentrated optical power delivery such as delicate eye microsurgery high-speed fiber-optic telecommunications and the precise cutting and welding of thick steel plates in heavy industrial manufacturing processes worldwide.","Laser 技术产生 intense highly focused beam of coherent light 其中所有 individual light waves 以 exactly the same precise wavelength and phase oscillate in perfect synchrony with one another enabling 需要 extreme precision and concentrated optical power delivery 的 applications 如 delicate eye microsurgery high-speed fiber-optic telecommunications and the precise cutting and welding of thick steel plates in heavy industrial manufacturing processes worldwide"],
  ["lens","Science and Research","透镜","光学镜片","The compound optical microscope uses a carefully calibrated system of multiple precision-ground glass lens arranged in a specific configuration along the vertical optical axis to produce highly magnified clear images of extremely tiny specimens such as individual living cells and subcellular organelles that would otherwise remain completely invisible and undetectable to the unaided naked human eye alone without the assistance of such sophisticated optical magnification instrumentation and technology.","Compound optical microscope 使用 a carefully calibrated system of multiple precision-ground glass lens arranged in a specific configuration along the vertical optical axis 以 produce highly magnified clear images of extremely tiny specimens such as individual living cells and subcellular organelles 否则这些 specimen 将 remain completely invisible and undetectable to the unaided naked human eye alone without the assistance of such sophisticated optical magnification instrumentation and technology"],
  ["lever","Science and Research","杠杆","简单机械","A lever is one of the six fundamental classical simple machines identified by ancient Greek engineers and mathematicians that amplifies an input effort force applied at one point along a rigid beam rotating around a fixed pivot point called the fulcrum to produce a larger output force capable of lifting or moving a heavy load object positioned at a different location along the same beam with much less muscular effort required from the human operator performing the lifting or moving task.","Lever 是 ancient Greek engineers and mathematicians identified 的 six fundamental classical simple machines 之一 它 amplifies an input effort force applied at one point along a rigid beam rotating around a fixed pivot point called the fulcrum 以 produce a larger output force capable of lifting or moving a heavy load object positioned at a different location along the same beam 而 human operator performing the lifting or moving task 所需的 muscular effort 大大减少"],
  ["magnet","Science and Research","磁铁","磁性物体","A permanent magnet creates an invisible three-dimensional magnetic field in the space surrounding it that can attract or repel certain other magnetic materials such as those containing the ferromagnetic elements iron nickel and cobalt without requiring any direct physical contact between the magnet and the distant object being acted upon through the empty space separating them sometimes across surprisingly large distances relative to the physical size of the magnet itself.","Permanent magnet 在其周围的 space 中 creates an invisible three-dimensional magnetic field 可以 attract or repel 某些其他 magnetic materials 例如那些含有 ferromagnetic elements iron nickel and cobalt 的材料 而无需 magnet 和 being acted upon through the empty space separating them 的 distant object 之间的 any direct physical contact 有时跨越 surprisingly large distances relative to the physical size of the magnet itself"],
  ["mass","Science and Research","质量","物质数量","In physics mass is a fundamental intrinsic property of all matter that measures an object's inherent resistance to being accelerated when a net external force is applied to it a concept known as inertia and is quite distinct from the related but separate concept of weight which depends on the local strength of the gravitational field in which the object happens to be located at any given moment in time and space.","在物理学中 mass 是所有物质的一个 fundamental intrinsic property 它 measures an object's inherent resistance to being accelerated when a net external force is applied to it 这个概念称为 inertia 与 related but separate concept of weight  quite distinct 后者取决于 object 在任何 given moment in time and space happens to be located 的 gravitational field 的 local strength"],
  ["matter","Science and Research","物质","实体存在","All ordinary matter in the observable universe that we can directly detect and study with our scientific instruments is composed of atoms which are themselves built from just three types of fundamental subatomic particles namely positively charged protons and electrically neutral neutrons tightly bound together in the dense central atomic nucleus surrounded by a diffuse cloud of much lighter negatively charged electrons orbiting at various discrete distances and energy levels around that central nuclear core region.","Observable universe 中我们可以 directly detect and study with our scientific instruments 的所有 ordinary matter 都是由 atoms composed 的 而 atoms 本身又由 just three types of fundamental subatomic particles built 即 positively charged protons 和 electrically neutral neutrons tightly bound together 在 dense central atomic nucleus 中 周围环绕着 much lighter negatively charged electrons 的 diffuse cloud orbiting at various discrete distances and energy levels around that central nuclear core region"],
  ["melting","Science and Research","熔化","固体液化","The melting point of a pure crystalline solid substance is a characteristic physical property that can be used to help identify an unknown chemical compound because different pure substances melt at sharply defined and highly reproducible temperatures under standard atmospheric pressure conditions at sea level whereas impure mixtures typically melt over a broader and less well-defined temperature range that begins at a lower temperature than the pure substance alone would exhibit under otherwise identical heating and environmental measurement conditions.","Pure crystalline solid substance 的 melting point 是一个 characteristic physical property 可用于帮助 identify an unknown chemical compound 因为不同的 pure substances 在 standard atmospheric pressure conditions at sea level 下 melt at sharply defined and highly reproducible temperatures 而 impure mixtures 通常 melt over a broader and less well-defined temperature range 该范围始于比 pure substance alone would exhibit under otherwise identical heating and environmental measurement conditions 更低的温度"],
  ["meteor","Science and Research","流星","太空碎片","When a small rocky or metallic fragment of space debris enters the Earth's upper atmosphere at extremely high velocities typically exceeding twenty kilometers per second the intense friction with air molecules causes it to heat up so rapidly and intensely that it becomes a glowing streak of incandescent white light racing across the night sky a phenomenon commonly called a shooting star or more scientifically accurately termed a meteor by professional astronomers and planetary scientists studying near-Earth objects and solar system debris.","当 a small rocky or metallic fragment of space debris 以 extremely high velocities typically exceeding twenty kilometers per second enters the Earth's upper atmosphere 与 air molecules 的 intense friction 使其 so rapidly and intensely heat up 以至于它 becomes a glowing streak of incandescent white light racing across the night sky 这种现象通常称为 shooting star 或更 scientifically accurately termed a meteor by professional astronomers and planetary scientists studying near-Earth objects and solar system debris"],
  ["microbe","Science and Research","微生物","微小生物","Not all microbe that exist in the natural environment are harmful to humans in fact the vast majority of bacterial and fungal species living freely in soil water and even on and within our own bodies play essential beneficial roles in maintaining the health and proper functioning of ecosystems and individual organisms through processes such as nutrient cycling decomposition of organic waste materials and protection against colonization by genuinely pathogenic disease-causing microorganisms.","并非 natural environment 中存在的所有 microbe 都对人类 harmful 事实上绝大多数生活在 soil water 甚至我们自身 bodies on and within 的 bacterial and fungal species 通过 nutrient cycling decomposition of organic waste materials and protection against colonization by genuinely pathogenic disease-causing microorganisms 等过程 play essential beneficial roles in maintaining the health and proper functioning of ecosystems and individual organisms"],
  ["microscope","Science and Research","显微镜","放大仪器","The electron microscope can magnify biological specimens up to two million times their actual physical size revealing the intricate internal structural details of individual organelles within living cells and even the precise spatial arrangement of individual atoms within crystalline materials at a level of resolution that would have seemed like pure science fiction fantasy to scientists working just a single generation ago before these remarkable technological advances became widely available in research laboratories worldwide.","Electron microscope 可以将 biological specimens magnify up to two million times their actual physical size  revealing the intricate internal structural details of individual organelles within living cells 甚至 the precise spatial arrangement of individual atoms within crystalline materials 其 resolution 水平在仅仅 a single generation ago 在 these remarkable technological advances became widely available in research laboratories worldwide 之前对 scientists 来说 would have seemed like pure science fiction fantasy"],
  ["mineral","Science and Research","矿物","天然无机物","Geologists classify mineral as naturally occurring inorganic solid substances with a specific and well-defined repeating internal crystalline atomic structure and a characteristic chemical composition or range of compositions that can be expressed by a standardized chemical formula such as silicon dioxide for the common rock-forming mineral quartz found abundantly in continental crustal rocks across every major tectonic plate on the surface of our planet Earth.","Geologists classify mineral 为 naturally occurring inorganic solid substances 具有 specific and well-defined repeating internal crystalline atomic structure 和 characteristic chemical composition or range of compositions that can be expressed by a standardized chemical formula 例如 common rock-forming mineral quartz 的 silicon dioxide  found abundantly in continental crustal rocks across every major tectonic plate on the surface of our planet Earth"],
  ["momentum","Science and Research","动量","运动惯性","The principle of conservation of linear momentum states that the total momentum of an isolated system of interacting particles or objects remains absolutely constant over time provided that no net external forces from outside the defined system boundaries act upon any of the component particles or objects within it which is why when a moving billiard ball strikes a stationary one on a smooth level table the first ball slows down while the second ball begins moving in the same original direction with approximately the same speed that the first ball initially possessed before the collision occurred.","Principle of conservation of linear momentum 指出 只要 no net external forces from outside the defined system boundaries act upon any of the component particles or objects within it 一个由 interacting particles or objects 组成的 isolated system 的 total momentum  over time remains absolutely constant 这就是为什么当 moving billiard ball 在 smooth level table 上 strikes a stationary one 时 first ball slows down 而 second ball begins moving in the same original direction 其速度 approximately the same speed that the first ball initially possessed before the collision occurred"],
  ["mutation","Science and Research","突变","基因变化","A random genetic mutation occurring in the DNA sequence of a single reproductive cell can sometimes produce a novel inherited trait that confers even a very slight survival or reproductive advantage to the individual organism carrying that particular altered gene variant compared to other members of its species lacking the mutation which over many successive generations of natural selection can gradually increase the frequency of that originally rare beneficial genetic variant throughout the entire interbreeding population in a particular local environmental setting and ecological context.","发生在 a single reproductive cell 的 DNA sequence 中的 random genetic mutation 有时可以 produce a novel inherited trait that confers even a very slight survival or reproductive advantage to the individual organism carrying that particular altered gene variant 与 lacking the mutation 的其 species 的 other members 相比 经过 natural selection 的 many successive generations 可以 gradually increase the frequency of that originally rare beneficial genetic variant throughout the entire interbreeding population in a particular local environmental setting and ecological context"],
  ["neutron","Science and Research","中子","核子粒子","The atomic nucleus of most common chemical elements contains both positively charged protons and electrically neutral neutron tightly bound together by the extremely powerful but very short-range strong nuclear fundamental force which overcomes the intense mutual electrostatic repulsion between the crowded positively charged protons confined within the incredibly tiny volume of the dense central nucleus at the very heart of every single atom in the physical universe around us.","大多数常见 chemical elements 的 atomic nucleus 包含 positively charged protons 和 electrically neutral neutron 由 extremely powerful but very short-range strong nuclear fundamental force tightly bound together 该力克服了 crowded positively charged protons  confined within the incredibly tiny volume of the dense central nucleus at the very heart of every single atom in the physical universe around us 之间的 intense mutual electrostatic repulsion"],
  ["nucleus","Science and Research","核","中心结构","The dense central nucleus of an atom which contains over ninety-nine point nine percent of the atom's total mass but occupies only about one trillionth of its total physical volume is composed of positively charged protons and uncharged neutrons held together by the strong nuclear force and surrounded at relatively enormous distances by a diffuse cloud of much lighter negatively charged electrons orbiting in specific quantized energy shells around that incredibly tiny and unimaginably dense nuclear core region at the very center of every atom that makes up all ordinary matter in our physical world.","Atom 的 dense central nucleus 包含 over ninety-nine point nine percent of the atom's total mass 但仅 occupy about one trillionth of its total physical volume 由 positively charged protons 和 uncharged neutrons composed 由 strong nuclear force held together 并由 much lighter negatively charged electrons 的 diffuse cloud surrounded at relatively enormous distances orbiting in specific quantized energy shells around that incredibly tiny and unimaginably dense nuclear core region at the very center of every atom that makes up all ordinary matter in our physical world"],
  ["observe","Science and Research","观察","科学观测","The researchers set up a network of automated motion-sensitive cameras throughout the dense tropical rainforest to observe the natural behavior of elusive nocturnal wildlife species in their undisturbed native habitat without the potentially disturbing and behavior-altering physical presence of human scientific observers nearby that might cause the animals to modify their normal activity patterns and movement routines in response to the perceived foreign intrusion into their familiar home territory.","研究人员在 dense tropical rainforest 中设置了 automated motion-sensitive cameras 的 network 以 observe elusive nocturnal wildlife species 在它们 undisturbed native habitat 中的 natural behavior 而无需 human scientific observers 的 potentially disturbing and behavior-altering physical presence nearby 这可能导致 animals modify their normal activity patterns and movement routines in response to the perceived foreign intrusion into their familiar home territory"],
  ["orbit","Science and Research","轨道","天体运行","Artificial satellites placed into low Earth orbit at altitudes ranging from approximately two hundred to two thousand kilometers above our planet's surface complete one full revolution around the Earth roughly every ninety minutes traveling at blistering speeds of nearly twenty-eight thousand kilometers per hour to balance the inward pull of Earth's gravitational attraction against their natural tendency to continue moving forward in a straight line through the frictionless vacuum of empty space according to the fundamental physical principles of orbital mechanics first described by Isaac Newton over three centuries ago.","放置在 altitudes ranging from approximately two hundred to two thousand kilometers above our planet's surface 的 low Earth orbit 中的人造 satellites 大约每九十分钟 complete one full revolution around the Earth 以 nearly twenty-eight thousand kilometers per hour 的 blistering speeds traveling 以 balance the inward pull of Earth's gravitational attraction against their natural tendency to continue moving forward in a straight line through the frictionless vacuum of empty space 根据 Isaac Newton over three centuries ago 首次描述的 orbital mechanics 的 fundamental physical principles"],
  ["organism","Science and Research","生物体","生命个体","Every living organism from the simplest single-celled bacterium to the largest blue whale that has ever inhabited the Earth's vast oceans relies on the same fundamental set of biochemical processes including cellular respiration protein synthesis and DNA replication to maintain the complex organized state of matter and energy flow that distinguishes living biological entities from the non-living inanimate physical world of rocks minerals water and atmospheric gases that surrounds and sustains them all throughout their finite individual lifespans and across the endless generations of evolutionary time.","从 simplest single-celled bacterium 到曾经 inhabit 地球广阔海洋的 largest blue whale 每个 living organism 都依赖于同一套 fundamental set of biochemical processes 包括 cellular respiration protein synthesis 和 DNA replication 以 maintain the complex organized state of matter and energy flow that distinguishes living biological entities from the non-living inanimate physical world of rocks minerals water and atmospheric gases that surrounds and sustains them all throughout their finite individual lifespans and across the endless generations of evolutionary time"],
  ["oxide","Science and Research","氧化物","氧的化合物","Iron oxide commonly known as rust forms when metallic iron is exposed to both oxygen and moisture simultaneously over an extended period of time through a slow spontaneous electrochemical corrosion process that gradually and relentlessly converts the strong silvery-gray elemental metal into a weak flaky reddish-brown powdery substance that eventually crumbles away to nothing if the destructive corrosive chemical reaction is allowed to continue unchecked and unprotected against the surrounding environmental elements over many months and years of continuous outdoor exposure.","通常称为 rust 的 Iron oxide 当 metallic iron 在 extended period of time 内 simultaneously exposed 于 oxygen 和 moisture 时形成 通过 a slow spontaneous electrochemical corrosion process 逐渐且 relentlessly converts the strong silvery-gray elemental metal 为 a weak flaky reddish-brown powdery substance 如果 destructive corrosive chemical reaction 被 allowed to continue unchecked and unprotected against the surrounding environmental elements over many months and years of continuous outdoor exposure 最终 crumbles away to nothing"],
  ["particle","Science and Research","粒子","微小单位","Physicists use enormous particle accelerator facilities such as the Large Hadron Collider at CERN spanning several kilometers in underground circular tunnel diameter to smash subatomic particle together at velocities approaching the speed of light itself in order to briefly recreate the extreme conditions of unimaginably high energy and density that existed during the first tiny fraction of a second immediately following the Big Bang at the very birth of our universe some thirteen point eight billion years ago in the distant cosmic past.","物理学家使用 enormous particle accelerator facilities 如 CERN 的 Large Hadron Collider spanning several kilometers in underground circular tunnel diameter 以接近光速的 velocities smash subatomic particle together 以 briefly recreate 在约十三点八亿年前在遥远宇宙过去宇宙诞生之初 Big Bang 后 immediately following 的 the very first tiny fraction of a second 期间存在的 extreme conditions of unimaginably high energy and density"],
  ["petri","Science and Research","培养皿","实验容器","The microbiologist carefully streaked a small sample of the unknown bacterial culture onto the surface of a sterile nutrient agar growth medium contained within a standard disposable plastic petri dish and then placed it upside down into a warm dark incubation chamber set to thirty-seven degrees Celsius to allow the individual bacterial cells to multiply and form visible isolated colonies over the following twenty-four to forty-eight hour growth and incubation period before further analysis could begin.","Microbiologist 将 unknown bacterial culture 的 small sample carefully streaked 到包含在 standard disposable plastic petri dish 中的 sterile nutrient agar growth medium 的表面上 然后将其 upside down placed into a warm dark incubation chamber set to thirty-seven degrees Celsius 以在 further analysis could begin 之前的 following twenty-four to forty-eight hour growth and incubation period 内 allow the individual bacterial cells to multiply and form visible isolated colonies"],
  ["phase","Science and Research","相","物质状态","Water is a particularly remarkable chemical substance because it is one of the very few naturally occurring materials on Earth that can exist in all three common classical phase of matter namely solid ice liquid water and gaseous water vapor within the relatively narrow and easily accessible range of ambient temperature and atmospheric pressure conditions that prevail naturally across most of our planet's habitable surface environment throughout the changing seasons of the annual climatic cycle in temperate geographic regions of the world.","Water 是一种 particularly remarkable chemical substance 因为它是地球上 very few naturally occurring materials 之一 可以在 all three common classical phase of matter 即 solid ice liquid water 和 gaseous water vapor 中存在 在 naturally prevail across most of our planet's habitable surface environment throughout the changing seasons of the annual climatic cycle in temperate geographic regions of the world 的 relatively narrow and easily accessible range of ambient temperature and atmospheric pressure conditions 内"],
  ["plasma","Science and Research","等离子体","电离气体","Plasma sometimes described as the fourth fundamental state of matter distinct from solids liquids and ordinary gases consists of an extremely hot electrically conductive ionized gas in which a significant fraction of the original neutral atoms or molecules have been stripped of one or more of their bound electrons creating a turbulent and highly dynamic electrically charged mixture of freely moving positively charged atomic ions and negatively charged liberated electrons that responds strongly and collectively to externally applied electromagnetic fields and forces in complex and often quite surprising ways.","有时被描述为与 solids liquids 和 ordinary gases 不同的 fourth fundamental state of matter 的 Plasma 由 extremely hot electrically conductive ionized gas consists 其中 a significant fraction of the original neutral atoms or molecules 已被 stripped of one or more of their bound electrons creating a turbulent and highly dynamic electrically charged mixture of freely moving positively charged atomic ions and negatively charged liberated electrons that responds strongly and collectively to externally applied electromagnetic fields and forces in complex and often quite surprising ways"],
  ["polymer","Science and Research","聚合物","高分子","Synthetic organic polymer such as polyethylene and polypropylene have become absolutely ubiquitous in modern daily life with global annual production now exceeding four hundred million metric tons because these versatile inexpensive lightweight and easily moldable plastic materials can be manufactured into an almost limitless variety of useful everyday consumer products from food packaging and beverage containers to clothing fibers vehicle components and sophisticated medical devices used in life-saving surgical procedures every single day.","Synthetic organic polymer 如 polyethylene 和 polypropylene 已成为 modern daily life 中 absolutely ubiquitous 全球 annual production 现在 exceeding four hundred million metric tons 因为这些 versatile inexpensive lightweight and easily moldable plastic materials 可以 manufactured into an almost limitless variety of useful everyday consumer products 从 food packaging 和 beverage containers 到 clothing fibers vehicle components 和 sophisticated medical devices used in life-saving surgical procedures every single day"],
  ["precipitate","Science and Research","沉淀","析出固体","When a solution of dissolved silver nitrate is carefully mixed with a solution of dissolved sodium chloride in a glass beaker under standard laboratory conditions a white solid precipitate of insoluble silver chloride immediately forms and gradually settles to the bottom of the container as a fine chalky powder demonstrating the classic double displacement chemical reaction between two soluble ionic salt compounds that produces an insoluble solid product that separates from the remaining clear liquid supernatant solution above it.","当 dissolved silver nitrate 的溶液在 standard laboratory conditions 下在 glass beaker 中与 dissolved sodium chloride 的溶液 carefully mixed 时 a white solid precipitate of insoluble silver chloride immediately forms and gradually settles to the bottom of the container as a fine chalky powder demonstrated 两种 soluble ionic salt compounds 之间的 classic double displacement chemical reaction 产生一种 insoluble solid product that separates from the remaining clear liquid supernatant solution above it"],
  ["probe","Science and Research","探测器","探查工具","The deep-space scientific probe traveled for over nine years through the cold vacuum of interplanetary space covering a total distance of more than five billion kilometers before finally reaching its intended destination at the distant dwarf planet Pluto and its system of five known moons located at the outermost fringes of our solar system where it captured the first detailed close-up images and scientific measurements ever obtained of this mysterious and previously unexplored frozen world.","Deep-space scientific probe 在 cold vacuum of interplanetary space 中 traveled for over nine years covering a total distance of more than five billion kilometers 然后 finally reaching its intended destination at the distant dwarf planet Pluto and its system of five known moons located at the outermost fringes of our solar system 在那里它 capture 了有史以来第一次获得的对这个神秘且 previously unexplored frozen world 的 detailed close-up images and scientific measurements"],
  ["protein","Science and Research","蛋白质","生物分子","Protein are large complex biological macromolecules composed of long chains of smaller amino acid building blocks folded into precise and intricate three-dimensional shapes that determine their specific biological functions within living cells and organisms ranging from catalyzing metabolic chemical reactions as specialized enzymes to providing essential mechanical structural support to cells and tissues and transporting vital nutrient molecules throughout the complex internal circulatory systems of multicellular plants and animals across the natural world.","Protein 是 large complex biological macromolecules composed of long chains of smaller amino acid building blocks folded into precise and intricate three-dimensional shapes that determine their specific biological functions within living cells and organisms  ranging from catalyzing metabolic chemical reactions as specialized enzymes 到 providing essential mechanical structural support to cells and tissues 和 transporting vital nutrient molecules throughout the complex internal circulatory systems of multicellular plants and animals across the natural world"],
  ["proton","Science and Research","质子","正电粒子","The number of positively charged proton present in the atomic nucleus of an element determines its unique atomic number and therefore its fundamental chemical identity and position in the periodic table of the elements with hydrogen having just a single proton while uranium the heaviest naturally occurring element found in significant quantities on Earth contains exactly ninety-two protons densely packed together within its massive and inherently unstable radioactive atomic nucleus.","Positively charged proton present in an element 的 atomic nucleus 中的数量决定了其独特的 atomic number 以及其在 periodic table of the elements 中的 fundamental chemical identity and position  hydrogen 仅有一个 single proton 而 uranium  the heaviest naturally occurring element found in significant quantities on Earth 在其 massive and inherently unstable radioactive atomic nucleus 中 densely packed together exactly ninety-two protons"],
  ["quantum","Science and Research","量子","物理基本","Quantum mechanics the fundamental physical theory that governs the behavior of matter and energy at the atomic and subatomic scale describes a strange and deeply counterintuitive microscopic world in which individual particles can exist in multiple different states simultaneously until measured and can instantaneously influence each other's properties across arbitrarily large distances through a mysterious phenomenon that Albert Einstein famously referred to as spooky action at a distance between entangled quantum particles separated by vast expanses of empty space and time.","Quantum mechanics the fundamental physical theory that governs the behavior of matter and energy at the atomic and subatomic scale 描述了一个 strange and deeply counterintuitive microscopic world 在这个世界中 individual particles can exist in multiple different states simultaneously until measured 并且可以通过 Albert Einstein famously referred to as spooky action at a distance 的 mysterious phenomenon across arbitrarily large distances instantaneously influence each other's properties between entangled quantum particles separated by vast expanses of empty space and time"],
  ["radiation","Science and Research","辐射","能量发射","Prolonged exposure to high levels of ionizing nuclear radiation can cause severe and potentially irreversible damage to the delicate DNA molecules within living cells leading to an increased lifetime risk of developing various types of cancer and other serious radiation-induced genetic illnesses which is why extreme caution and multiple layers of protective shielding are always required whenever anyone works in environments where significant sources of ionizing radioactive materials are present and being actively handled by trained professionals wearing specialized protective equipment.","Prolonged exposure 于 high levels of ionizing nuclear radiation 可对 living cells 内 delicate DNA molecules 造成 severe and potentially irreversible damage  leading to an increased lifetime risk of developing various types of cancer and other serious radiation-induced genetic illnesses 这就是为什么每当在 significant sources of ionizing radioactive materials are present and being actively handled by trained professionals wearing specialized protective equipment 的环境中工作时总是需要 extreme caution and multiple layers of protective shielding"],
  ["ray","Science and Research","射线","能量束","Cosmic ray are highly energetic subatomic particles predominantly consisting of bare protons and heavier atomic nuclei that originate from distant astrophysical sources far beyond our own solar system such as the powerful shockwaves of ancient supernova explosions and the intense radiation beams emitted by rapidly rotating neutron stars and actively feeding supermassive black holes at the centers of remote galaxies scattered throughout the vast observable universe around us in every direction we can possibly look with our most sensitive and sophisticated astronomical instruments.","Cosmic ray 是 highly energetic subatomic particles predominantly consisting of bare protons and heavier atomic nuclei 它们 originate from distant astrophysical sources far beyond our own solar system 例如 ancient supernova explosions 的 powerful shockwaves 和 rapidly rotating neutron stars and actively feeding supermassive black holes at the centers of remote galaxies scattered throughout the vast observable universe around us in every direction we can possibly look with our most sensitive and sophisticated astronomical instruments 所 emit 的 intense radiation beams"],
  ["reaction","Science and Research","反应","化学变化","The rate of a chemical reaction typically increases significantly with rising temperature because at higher temperatures a larger proportion of the colliding reactant molecules possess the minimum required activation energy necessary to break their existing chemical bonds and successfully rearrange into the new molecular configurations and bonding arrangements that characterize the desired final product compounds of that particular chemical transformation process being studied or utilized industrially.","Chemical reaction 的速率通常随温度升高而显著增加 因为在较高温度下 a larger proportion of the colliding reactant molecules possess the minimum required activation energy necessary to break their existing chemical bonds 并 successfully rearrange into the new molecular configurations and bonding arrangements that characterize the desired final product compounds of that particular chemical transformation process being studied or utilized industrially"],
  ["reagent","Science and Research","试剂","化学试药","Analytical chemists must always handle potentially hazardous laboratory reagent with extreme care and strict adherence to established safety protocols including wearing appropriate personal protective equipment such as chemical-resistant gloves and safety goggles and working only within properly functioning fume extraction hoods when dealing with volatile toxic or corrosive chemical substances that could pose significant immediate or long-term health risks to laboratory personnel if accidentally inhaled ingested or absorbed through unprotected skin contact in the workplace.","Analytical chemists 必须始终以 extreme care and strict adherence to established safety protocols handle potentially hazardous laboratory reagent 包括 wearing appropriate personal protective equipment such as chemical-resistant gloves and safety goggles 并在处理 volatile toxic or corrosive chemical substances 时仅 working only within properly functioning fume extraction hoods 这些物质如果 accidentally inhaled ingested or absorbed through unprotected skin contact in the workplace 可能对 laboratory personnel 构成 significant immediate or long-term health risks"],
  ["replicate","Science and Research","复制","实验重复","Before any major scientific discovery can be widely accepted as valid and reliable by the broader international research community other independent laboratory groups at different institutions around the world must be able to successfully replicate the original experimental results under carefully controlled conditions producing substantially the same observed outcomes using the same published experimental procedures and analytical methods described in the original peer-reviewed scientific publication that first reported the novel and potentially important finding to the wider academic world.","在任何 major scientific discovery 能被 broader international research community widely accepted as valid and reliable 之前世界各地的 different institutions 的 other independent laboratory groups 必须能够在 carefully controlled conditions 下 successfully replicate the original experimental results 使用 original peer-reviewed scientific publication that first reported the novel and potentially important finding to the wider academic world 中描述的 same published experimental procedures and analytical methods producing substantially the same observed outcomes"],
  ["resist","Science and Research","抵抗","对抗外力","Certain species of bacteria have evolved the ability to resist the powerful antibiotic drugs that were previously capable of easily killing them through the gradual evolutionary accumulation over many successive bacterial generations of random genetic mutations that happen to confer even a very slight survival advantage to those particular individual bacterial cells carrying the protective altered genes when they are repeatedly exposed to the antibiotic compounds over extended periods of treatment time in hospital patients and agricultural livestock populations globally.","某些 bacteria 的 species 已经 evolve 了 resist the powerful antibiotic drugs 的能力 这些药物以前 capable of easily killing them 通过在 many successive bacterial generations 中 gradual evolutionary accumulation of random genetic mutations that happen to confer even a very slight survival advantage to those particular individual bacterial cells carrying the protective altered genes 当它们在 hospital patients and agricultural livestock populations globally 中 over extended periods of treatment time repeatedly exposed 于 antibiotic compounds 时"],
  ["simulate","Science and Research","模拟","仿真实验","Powerful supercomputers running highly sophisticated climate models can simulate the enormously complex interacting physical chemical and biological processes that govern the behavior of Earth's entire global atmosphere and ocean circulation systems over timescales spanning many decades and even centuries into the hypothetical future based on different plausible greenhouse gas emission scenarios and their projected warming impacts on worldwide average temperatures precipitation patterns and extreme weather event frequency and intensity across every major continental region on our rapidly changing warming planet.","运行 highly sophisticated climate models 的 powerful supercomputers 可以 simulate 支配 Earth's entire global atmosphere and ocean circulation systems 行为的 enormously complex interacting physical chemical and biological processes 跨越 many decades and even centuries 的时间尺度进入 hypothetical future 基于 different plausible greenhouse gas emission scenarios and their projected warming impacts on worldwide average temperatures precipitation patterns and extreme weather event frequency and intensity across every major continental region on our rapidly changing warming planet"],
  ["soluble","Science and Research","可溶的","能够溶解","Vitamin C also known chemically as ascorbic acid is a water-soluble essential micronutrient that the human body cannot synthesize or store in significant amounts for extended periods of time and must therefore be regularly consumed through a balanced daily diet containing adequate quantities of fresh fruits and green leafy vegetables to prevent the development of the historically feared deficiency disease known as scurvy that once plagued long-distance sailors on extended ocean voyages lasting many months without access to fresh food supplies.","Vitamin C 化学上也称为 ascorbic acid 是一种 water-soluble essential micronutrient 人体不能 synthesize or store in significant amounts for extended periods of time 因此必须通过含有 adequate quantities of fresh fruits and green leafy vegetables 的 balanced daily diet regularly consumed 以 prevent 历史上 feared 的 deficiency disease known as scurvy 的 development 这种病 once plagued long-distance sailors on extended ocean voyages lasting many months without access to fresh food supplies"],
  ["spectrum","Science and Research","光谱","频率范围","When ordinary white sunlight passes through a glass prism the different constituent wavelength components that together make up what we perceive as colorless white light are bent by slightly different amounts as they enter and exit the denser glass material causing them to spread out and separate spatially into the familiar continuous rainbow-like visible spectrum of distinct colors ranging from long-wavelength red at one end through orange yellow green and blue to short-wavelength violet at the opposite end of the observable visible light wavelength range detectable by the light-sensitive cone receptor cells in our human eyes.","当普通白色阳光穿过 glass prism 时 共同构成我们 perceive as colorless white light 的不同 constituent wavelength components 在进入和离开 denser glass material 时被 slightly different amounts bent 导致它们 spread out and separate spatially into the familiar continuous rainbow-like visible spectrum of distinct colors 从一端的 long-wavelength red through orange yellow green and blue 到 opposite end of the observable visible light wavelength range 的 short-wavelength violet 可由我们人类眼睛中的 light-sensitive cone receptor cells detectable"],
  ["spore","Science and Research","孢子","繁殖细胞","Fungi reproduce by releasing enormous numbers of microscopic airborne spore into the surrounding environment that can be carried by wind currents over surprisingly large distances before eventually settling and if conditions of adequate moisture warmth and nutrient availability happen to be favorable germinating into new fungal colonies that will eventually in turn produce their own spore and continue the endless biological cycle of fungal reproduction and dispersal across the natural landscape from one generation to the next throughout the changing seasons of each passing year.","Fungi 通过向周围环境 releasing enormous numbers of microscopic airborne spore 来 reproduce 这些 spore 可以被 wind currents carried over surprisingly large distances 然后 eventually settling 如果 adequate moisture warmth and nutrient availability 的条件 happen to be favorable 就会 germinating into new fungal colonies 这些 colonies eventually 又 produce their own spore 并 continue the endless biological cycle of fungal reproduction and dispersal across the natural landscape from one generation to the next throughout the changing seasons of each passing year"],
  ["strain","Science and Research","菌株","生物变种","Medical researchers are urgently working to develop a new effective vaccine specifically targeting the latest highly mutated and unusually contagious strain of the influenza virus that has recently emerged and is spreading rapidly through densely populated urban areas across multiple continents straining healthcare systems and causing widespread concern among international public health authorities and government pandemic preparedness agencies worldwide about the potential for a severe global disease outbreak in the coming winter respiratory illness season.","Medical researchers 正在 urgently working to develop a new effective vaccine specifically targeting the latest highly mutated and unusually contagious strain of the influenza virus that has recently emerged and is spreading rapidly through densely populated urban areas across multiple continents straining healthcare systems and causing widespread concern among international public health authorities and government pandemic preparedness agencies worldwide about the potential for a severe global disease outbreak in the coming winter respiratory illness season"],
  ["telescope","Science and Research","望远镜","天文观测","The newly launched James Webb Space Telescope positioned nearly one point five million kilometers from Earth at a gravitationally stable point in space known as the second Sun-Earth Lagrange point can peer deep into the distant cosmos capturing faint infrared light from the very first primitive galaxies that began forming less than four hundred million years after the original Big Bang event that created our entire observable universe approximately thirteen point eight billion years ago in the unimaginably remote and ancient cosmic past.","Newly launched James Webb Space Telescope positioned nearly one point five million kilometers from Earth at a gravitationally stable point in space known as the second Sun-Earth Lagrange point 可以 deep into the distant cosmos peer capturing faint infrared light from the very first primitive galaxies that began forming less than four hundred million years after the original Big Bang event that created our entire observable universe approximately thirteen point eight billion years ago in the unimaginably remote and ancient cosmic past"],
  ["test","Science and Research","测试","实验验证","Before any new pharmaceutical drug can receive official regulatory approval for widespread clinical use in treating human patients it must first successfully pass through three sequential phases of rigorous randomized controlled clinical test involving increasingly large numbers of volunteer participants to convincingly demonstrate both its safety and its statistically meaningful medical efficacy compared to existing standard treatment options or a biologically inactive placebo control substance under carefully monitored and ethically supervised research conditions over a period of several years of systematic scientific investigation.","在任何新 pharmaceutical drug 可以 receive official regulatory approval for widespread clinical use in treating human patients 之前它必须首先 successfully pass through three sequential phases of rigorous randomized controlled clinical test involving increasingly large numbers of volunteer participants 以 convincingly demonstrate 其 safety 和与 existing standard treatment options or a biologically inactive placebo control substance 相比的 statistically meaningful medical efficacy 在 carefully monitored and ethically supervised research conditions 下 over a period of several years of systematic scientific investigation 之后"],
  ["theory","Science and Research","理论","科学解释","A robust scientific theory is far more than just a casual guess or an unsupported hunch about how something in the natural world might possibly work it represents instead a comprehensive well-substantiated and repeatedly tested explanatory framework that has survived rigorous experimental scrutiny and successfully made accurate predictions about future observations across a wide range of related phenomena over an extended period of time earning broad acceptance within the relevant scientific community as the best currently available explanation for the observed facts and evidence at hand based on the cumulative weight of all the available data and logical reasoning supporting it.","一个 robust scientific theory 远不止是 a casual guess or an unsupported hunch 关于自然世界中某事物可能如何运作 它代表的是一种 comprehensive well-substantiated and repeatedly tested explanatory framework 它 survived rigorous experimental scrutiny 并 successfully made accurate predictions about future observations across a wide range of related phenomena over an extended period of time earning broad acceptance within the relevant scientific community as the best currently available explanation for the observed facts and evidence at hand based on the cumulative weight of all the available data and logical reasoning supporting it"],
  ["tissue","Science and Research","组织","生物结构","The pathologist carefully examined thin stained slices of the patient's biopsied liver tissue under a high-powered laboratory microscope searching for any telltale microscopic cellular abnormalities or distinctive patterns of structural tissue damage that might help the medical team definitively diagnose the underlying cause of the patient's persistent and unexplained chronic illness that had been troubling them for over six months without any clear explanation or effective treatment yet identified.","Pathologist 在 high-powered laboratory microscope 下 carefully examined thin stained slices of the patient's biopsied liver tissue searching for any telltale microscopic cellular abnormalities or distinctive patterns of structural tissue damage that might help the medical team definitively diagnose the underlying cause of the patient's persistent and unexplained chronic illness that had been troubling them for over six months without any clear explanation or effective treatment yet identified"],
  ["torque","Science and Research","扭矩","旋转力","The powerful electric motor in modern high-performance electric vehicles delivers maximum driving torque almost instantly from a complete standstill providing breathtaking acceleration from zero to one hundred kilometers per hour in under three seconds for the fastest production models currently available on the commercial automotive market which is a level of straight-line performance that even the most expensive and exotic gasoline-powered supercars from just a single generation ago could only dream of ever possibly achieving in their wildest engineering ambitions and performance fantasies.","Modern high-performance electric vehicles 中 powerful electric motor 从 complete standstill almost instantly delivers maximum driving torque 提供从零到一百公里每小时在不到三秒内的 breathtaking acceleration 对于目前 commercial automotive market 上可用的最快 production models 而言 这种 straight-line performance 水平是仅仅 a single generation ago 的 even the most expensive and exotic gasoline-powered supercars 在其 wildest engineering ambitions and performance fantasies 中也 only dream of ever possibly achieving 的"],
  ["trial","Science and Research","试验","临床测试","Phase three clinical trial are the final and most extensive stage of human testing required before a newly developed pharmaceutical drug or medical treatment can be submitted for formal evaluation and potential approval by government regulatory agencies and typically involve many thousands of volunteer participants recruited from multiple different hospitals and medical research centers spread across numerous countries and continents around the world to ensure that the collected data on safety and efficacy is statistically robust and broadly generalizable across diverse patient demographic populations and geographical regions.","Phase three clinical trial 是新开发的 pharmaceutical drug or medical treatment 在可以 submitted for formal evaluation and potential approval by government regulatory agencies 之前所需的 human testing 的 final and most extensive stage 通常涉及从 spread across numerous countries and continents around the world 的 multiple different hospitals and medical research centers recruited 数千名 volunteer participants 以确保收集的关于 safety 和 efficacy 的数据在统计上是 robust 的且 broadly generalizable across diverse patient demographic populations and geographical regions"],
  ["vacuum","Science and Research","真空","无物质空间","Sound waves cannot propagate through the perfect vacuum of empty outer space because they require a material physical medium such as air water or solid metal consisting of atoms or molecules to mechanically transmit the traveling pattern of alternating compression and rarefaction regions from one physical location to another which is why the dramatic explosions and roaring engine sounds often depicted in science fiction movies set in the silent vastness of interstellar space are scientifically inaccurate and would in actual reality be completely inaudible and utterly silent to any nearby human observer or hypothetical alien listener positioned in the surrounding cosmic void.","Sound waves 不能通过 empty outer space 的 perfect vacuum propagate 因为它们需要 a material physical medium 如 air water or solid metal consisting of atoms or molecules 以 mechanically transmit the traveling pattern of alternating compression and rarefaction regions from one physical location to another 这就是为什么在 silent vastness of interstellar space 中设定的 science fiction movies 中经常 depict 的 dramatic explosions and roaring engine sounds 是 scientifically inaccurate 的 并且在 actual reality 中对于任何 nearby human observer or hypothetical alien listener positioned in the surrounding cosmic void 来说将是 completely inaudible and utterly silent 的"],
  ["velocity","Science and Research","速度","运动快慢","The escape velocity required for a spacecraft to permanently break free from the powerful gravitational pull of our planet Earth and journey onward into the vastness of interplanetary space without falling back down to the surface is approximately eleven point two kilometers per second or roughly forty thousand kilometers per hour which is over thirty times faster than the typical cruising speed of a commercial passenger jet airliner flying at maximum efficiency through the thin air at high altitude in the upper reaches of our planet's protective atmospheric layer surrounding the globe below.","Spacecraft 要 permanently break free from the powerful gravitational pull of our planet Earth and journey onward into the vastness of interplanetary space without falling back down to the surface 所需的 escape velocity 大约为 eleven point two kilometers per second 或 roughly forty thousand kilometers per hour 比 commercial passenger jet airliner at maximum efficiency through the thin air at high altitude in the upper reaches of our planet's protective atmospheric layer surrounding the globe below flying 的 typical cruising speed 快 over thirty times"],
  ["ventilation","Science and Research","通风","空气流通","Proper laboratory ventilation is absolutely critical for maintaining a safe and healthy working environment when handling volatile toxic or flammable chemical substances because the continuous flow of fresh filtered air through the workspace effectively removes and dilutes any potentially hazardous chemical vapors or fine airborne particulate matter that might otherwise gradually accumulate to dangerously high and potentially harmful airborne concentration levels within the enclosed and confined indoor space of the occupied laboratory room environment over the course of a busy working day.","在处理 volatile toxic or flammable chemical substances 时 Proper laboratory ventilation 对于 maintaining a safe and healthy working environment absolutely critical 因为 fresh filtered air 的 continuous flow through the workspace effectively removes and dilutes 任何 potentially hazardous chemical vapors or fine airborne particulate matter 否则它们可能在 the course of a busy working day 中 gradually accumulate to dangerously high and potentially harmful airborne concentration levels 在 enclosed and confined indoor space of the occupied laboratory room environment 内"],
  ["voltage","Science and Research","电压","电势差","The electrical transmission grid carries high-voltage alternating current electricity at many hundreds of thousands of volts from distant centralized power generating stations through a nationwide network of thick metal conducting cables suspended high above the ground on tall steel lattice towers stretching across the countryside for vast distances before eventually being stepped down to much lower and safer household voltage levels by local substation transformers for final distribution into individual residential homes apartments schools and business premises throughout every city town and village across the entire country.","Electrical transmission grid 将 high-voltage alternating current electricity at many hundreds of thousands of volts 从 distant centralized power generating stations 通过悬挂在 tall steel lattice towers 上的 thick metal conducting cables 组成的 nationwide network carries 跨越 countryside 的 vast distances stretching 然后最终被 local substation transformers stepped down to much lower and safer household voltage levels 以最终 distribution 到个体 residential homes apartments schools and business premises throughout every city town and village across the entire country"],
  ["volume","Science and Research","体积","空间占据","According to the well-established physical principle known as Charles Law the volume of a fixed quantity of an ideal gas maintained at a constant pressure will expand predictably when the temperature of that gas is increased because the constituent gas molecules gain additional kinetic energy and move around more vigorously on average colliding more frequently and with greater force against the internal walls of their flexible expandable containing vessel thereby gradually pushing the movable boundaries of the container outward and increasing the total physical space that the heated expanding gas now occupies within the newly enlarged containing volume available to it.","根据称为 Charles Law 的 well-established physical principle 保持在 constant pressure 下的 fixed quantity of an ideal gas 的 volume 将当该气体的温度升高时 predictably expand 因为 constituent gas molecules gain additional kinetic energy and move around more vigorously on average colliding more frequently and with greater force against the internal walls of their flexible expandable containing vessel  thereby gradually pushing the movable boundaries of the container outward 并 increasing the total physical space that the heated expanding gas now occupies within the newly enlarged containing volume available to it"],
  ["watt","Science and Research","瓦特","功率单位","A typical modern domestic LED light bulb consumes only about ten watt of electrical power to produce the same amount of visible illumination that would have previously required an old-fashioned incandescent filament bulb drawing approximately sixty watts from the household mains electricity supply representing an enormous improvement in household energy conversion efficiency of over eighty percent for the same usable light output delivered to the room being illuminated for reading and other everyday household tasks and activities.","一个 typical modern domestic LED light bulb 仅 consume about ten watt 的 electrical power 即可产生与 old-fashioned incandescent filament bulb drawing approximately sixty watts from the household mains electricity supply  previously required 相同数量的可见照明 representing an enormous improvement in household energy conversion efficiency of over eighty percent for the same usable light output delivered to the room being illuminated for reading and other everyday household tasks and activities"],
  ["wavelength","Science and Research","波长","波动距离","The characteristic wavelength of visible electromagnetic radiation determines the specific color that the human eye and brain perceive when light of that particular wavelength enters the eye and stimulates the three different types of color-sensitive cone receptor cells densely packed across the central region of the light-sensitive retina at the back of the eyeball with shorter wavelengths around four hundred nanometers appearing as violet and blue while longer wavelengths approaching seven hundred nanometers appear as various shades of orange and deep red to the conscious visual perception system of the human observer viewing the world around them.","Visible electromagnetic radiation 的 characteristic wavelength 决定了当该特定 wavelength 的 light enters the eye and stimulates 三种不同类型的 color-sensitive cone receptor cells densely packed across the central region of the light-sensitive retina at the back of the eyeball 时人眼和大脑 perceive 的 specific color  shorter wavelengths around four hundred nanometers appearing as violet and blue 而 longer wavelengths approaching seven hundred nanometers 在 human observer viewing the world around them 的 conscious visual perception system 中 appear as various shades of orange and deep red"],
];